# Stomp4J — core rules

Follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) and existing code in the same package.

## Stack

- Java 21, Maven multi-module, JPMS (`module-info.java` in every module).
- STOMP protocol library — no Spring, no Quarkus, no web UI.
- Logging: SLF4J only. Scripts: bash or JBang — [stomp4j-tooling-languages.mdc](stomp4j-tooling-languages.mdc).

## Modules

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `commons` | Wire format: `Message`, `Command`, `Headers`, `MessageBuffer` |
| `client` | `StompClient` API, transports (TCP/WebSocket), protocol versions 1.0–1.2 |
| `server` | `StompServer`, channels, sessions, handlers |

## Public API

- **Client:** `StompClient.create(url, …)` — factory methods only; implementation in `internal`.
- **Server:** `StompServer.builder()` — configure channels, handlers, authenticator.
- Do not expose `internal`, `channels`, or `session` packages without updating `module-info.java` deliberately.

## SPI extension

New transports or protocol versions:

1. Implement interface (`TransportProvider` or `Stomp`).
2. Register `provides` in `module-info.java`.
3. Add `META-INF/services/…` file under `client/src/main/resources/`.

## Never

- `System.out.println` — use SLF4J.
- Import `client.internal` or `server.channels` / `server.session` from outside their module.
- Add a framework (Spring, Quarkus) to production dependencies.

## When adding a feature

ARCHITECTURE.md §13 — domain spec → correct module → SPI if needed → **tiered tests** ([stomp4j-test-during-development.mdc](stomp4j-test-during-development.mdc)) → `mvn verify`.

## When fixing a test

Understand failure first; fix production code or test setup. Reuse `StompContainer`, `StompTestSupport`, and existing test infra. Follow [stomp4j-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc](stomp4j-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc).
